In addition, Mahaka, through Republika, has established a partnership to implement the PlastikPay  program.  This  initiative  encourages communities to protect the environment by depositing  used  plastic  bottles  through  Reverse Vending  Machine  (RVM)  units  connected  to  the PlastikPay  application.  Additionally,  the  program aligns with Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs)  Numbers  12,  13,  and  14,  focusing  on Environmental Protection and Plastic Usage.

The Company also maintains sustainable implementation in environmental aspects as part of  the  Company's operations. Throughout 2023, the  Company  carried  out  various  environmental management programs such as providing separate  landfifills  based  on  the  type  of  waste and hazardous waste, effifficient use of water, and electricity.

The Company is also committed to implementing several program  initiatives related to Energy Efficiency and an Environmentally Friendly Office (Green Office). Through this effort, the Company builds  employee  awareness  to  participate  and work  together  to  maintain  energy  efficiency  in order to create an environmentally friendly office climate.

More  specififically,  the  Company  continues  the efforts to maintain and improve the environmental quality that has been carried out in the previous year by doing the following things:

- 1. more effifficient use of electrical energy in the offiffice by turning offff lights when not in use;
- 2. more  effifficient  use  of  paper  by  converting documents into digital form and only printing when needed;
- 3. more  effifficient  use  of  water  in  toilets  by providing  stickers  on  toilets  to  use  water cautiously;

